    "solution": "1. Apparent weight during upward accelerated motion: P = m*(g + a).\n2. Substitute a = 4g: P = m*(g + 4g) = m * 5g.\n3. This state is called overload; the apparent weight is 5 times greater.\n4. P = 80 * 5 * 10 = 4000 N.",
    "answer": "P = 4000 N (5g overload)."
