    "given_data": "μ = 0.3\nSliding threshold: a = 0 (limiting static friction case)",
    "find_text": "α - ?",
    "solution": "1. At the beginning of sliding, static friction reaches its maximum: mg * sin(α) = μ * mg * cos(α).\n2. Therefore μ = sin(α) / cos(α) = tan(α).\n3. Hence tan(α) = 0.3.\n4. α = arctan(0.3) ≈ 16.7°.",
